# Instagram Credentials
# Choose ONE method below (workflow will auto-detect)

# ========================================
# METHOD 1: Personal Account (Recommended for GitHub Actions)
# ========================================
# Uses instagrapi - can upload local files directly
# Works in GitHub Actions without needing public URL
INSTAGRAM_USERNAME=your_instagram_username
INSTAGRAM_PASSWORD=your_instagram_password

# ========================================
# METHOD 2: Business Account (Graph API)
# ========================================
# Requires video to be publicly accessible via URL
# NOT recommended for GitHub Actions (cannot upload local files)
# Use only if you have CDN/server to host videos
# IG_USER_ID=your_instagram_user_id
# LONG_LIVED_TOKEN=your_long_lived_token
# APP_ID=your_app_id
# APP_SECRET=your_app_secret

# ========================================
# GitHub Actions Setup
# ========================================
# Add these as repository secrets:
# Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → New repository secret
#
# For METHOD 1 (Personal - Recommended):
#   - INSTAGRAM_USERNAME
#   - INSTAGRAM_PASSWORD
#
# For METHOD 2 (Business):
#   - IG_USER_ID
#   - LONG_LIVED_TOKEN

